T6	p 727 1047	The plague has already reached epidemic levels in 48 Asian countries and 53 African states, as well as in Brazil and the United States. It was detected in China in 1943, in Africa in 1947, and by 2005 it had begun to devastate orange groves in Florida. It hasn't reached Europe yet, but the insect that transmits it has.
